# Onscreen Assistant Backend API

A Flask-based backend API for an Onscreen Assistant system, supporting semantic search, chat, and note management.

---

## 🚀 Features

- Semantic search + LLM-based chat
- Add and store notes under topics
- Debug notes
- RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) support

---

## ⚙️ Setup Instructions

### 📝 Project Description

This project provides the backend API for an Onscreen Assistant that runs on every webpage via a browser extension or desktop integration.
It enables users to:
- Add personal notes categorized by topics
- Ask questions using semantic search and a language model (LLM)
- Retrieve past conversations
- Perform advanced Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) for deep contextual answers

The system uses:
- **Chroma** as a vector database for note storage and semantic search
- **HuggingFace Embeddings** for embedding user inputs
- **Firebase** to store chat history
- **Langchain** for orchestrating the semantic search + LLM pipeline

---

